textAfterTable: Event Detail Information Event Detail Information FLAS Fellowship Information Session for Graduate and Undergraduate Students Speaker Area Studies FLAS Coordinators Date Oct 29, 2012 Time 4:00 pm   Location Room 126, Library & Information Science Bldg, 501 E. Daniel, Champaign Sponsor International and Area Studies Centers Contact Lynn Charters E-Mail charterl@illinois.edu Phone 265-5186 Views 1404 Originating Calendar Global Health Initiative Events This information session will include presentations by the Area and International Centers FLAS coordinators. In addition to a general overview of FLAS fellowships and particular requirements for various Area Centers, you can get tips on how to write a successful application; what supporting documents you need; and who is appropriate for a recommendation. If you cannot make this session, there will be another session offered on Tuesday, October 30, at 4pm, in Room 126, Library & Information
